node.text: Getting all dolled up for the holidays and sharing my favorite “party pony” look with @allthingshairus! ♥️🙌🏻 Head to @allthingshairus, follow them and tag 3 friends on today’s daily post to enter their amazing 12 days of Christmas giveaway! For an even bigger prize, head to allthingshair.com for a chance to win the... drumroll please... grand prize! 🎁🎉 #ad #ATHAdvent @suavebeauty @nexxushaircare @lovebeautyandplanet

node.text: If you’ve ever been bored by the Bible, feeling as if you “should” enjoy reading it but simply do not, I hope this video encourages you today! Once I started spending time in the Word, as opposed to only reading what others had to say about it, my faith deepened and grew in a way I had never known before. I hope you enjoy!

node.title: How To Grow Your Love For Reading The Bible

node.text:
just a ‘lil beach bum(p) 🌊🤍🌴 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Hello for the first time in quite a while, y’all! Wow. I could never have predicted the new, much-slowed pace I’d be forced to take these past couple of months. I’ve always known that when I became a mother, I’d want to slow down… but I think the Lord knew that bringing me to an absolute halt was the only way to show me just what that would look like. Every single message and kind word has meant the world as I struggled through my first trimester (all the nausea & getting sick, fatigue and over-all funk 🥴) and let’s just say I have a whole new respect for all you mamas out there! I know every pregnancy is different, and while the past 14 weeks have been a bit rougher than I ever anticipated, I’m so thankful that I’m feeling better day by day and starting to feel like myself again! Not to mention SO over the moon about this little, precious life! If you’re in the weeds during the first few weeks, it gets better I promise. Thank you for the encouragement and kindness and grace you’ve shown me as I’ve been “off the grid.” While lots of it has been hard, lots of it has been GREAT, too. And I think it’s just going to get better and better! #firsttrimester #pregnancy #gosummersalt
⁣
“Truly my soul finds rest in God; my salvation comes from him.” Psalm 62:1

node.text:
We are having a baby! 👶🏻 Thrilled to share that little baby Bowman will join our little family early next year. Andrew and I are over the moon and so, so grateful to our Heavenly Father for this gift!!! For as long as I can remember, my deepest desire and ultimate dream in life has been to be a mama - I can’t believe the time has come. 😭
⁣
“Your eyes saw my unformed body; all the days ordained for me were written in your book before one of them came to be.” Psalm 139:16

Some of you may have noticed I’ve been gone for the past few weeks (thank you for all of your sweet messages!) and I can’t tell you how wonderful it is to finally share the news with y’all. Promise there will be more to share soon!

Also, please don’t be misled by all of the blue. 😂 We don’t know the gender yet, but can’t wait to find out as soon as possible! Any guesses?!

Thank you, thank you, thank you for sharing in our joy! 🤍 #pregnant

The @migolondrina Fourth of July collection JUST launched, and it is what my blue-and-white loving dreams are made of! 🤍🙌🏻   #sponsored
   
Each piece is hand embroidered in Oaxaca, Mexico and is nothing short of exquisite. Lightweight, colorful and incredibly comfortable, these pieces are my go-to all summer long and my favorite things to collect!  
 
Sizing: Since the style of Mi Golondrina pieces are relaxed and roomy, there’s a bit of flexibility. I own both XS and S, and am wearing an S here! The biggest key is bust size. If you are larger up top, I’d recommend going up a size. The Mi Golondrina team is so helpful with fit if you have any specific questions!
